#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:14
msgid "Boundary Representation (BREP) Modelling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:16
msgid ""
"Boundary representation (BREP) and mesh-based CAD systems are both used to "
"create and manipulate 3D models, but they differ in the way they represent "
"and store the models."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:20
msgid "Advantages of BREP-based CAD systems (e.g. build123d & SolidWorks):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:22
msgid ""
"Precision: BREP-based CAD systems use mathematical representations to define"
" the shape of an object, which allows for more precise and accurate modeling"
" of complex shapes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:25
msgid ""
"Topology: BREP-based CAD systems maintain topological information of the 3D "
"model, such as edges, faces and vertices. This allows for more robust and "
"stable modeling, such as Boolean operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:28
msgid ""
"Analytical modeling: BREP-based CAD systems can take advantage of the "
"topological information to perform analytical operations such as collision "
"detection, mass properties calculations, and finite element analysis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:31
msgid ""
"Features-based modeling: BREP-based CAD systems are often feature-based, "
"which means that the model is built by creating and modifying individual "
"features, such as holes, fillets, and chamfers. This allows for parametric "
"design and easy modification of the model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:35
msgid ""
"Efficient storage: BREP-based CAD systems use a compact representation to "
"store the 3D model, which is more efficient than storing a large number of "
"triangles used in mesh-based systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:40
msgid "Advantages of Mesh-based CAD systems (e.g. Blender, OpenSCAD):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:42
msgid ""
"Simplicity: Mesh-based CAD systems use a large number of triangles to "
"represent the surface of an object, which makes them easy to use and "
"understand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:44
msgid ""
"Real-time rendering: Mesh-based CAD systems can be rendered in real-time, "
"which is useful for applications such as video games and virtual reality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:46
msgid ""
"Flexibility: Mesh-based CAD systems can be easily exported to other 3D "
"modeling and animation software, which makes them a good choice for use in "
"the entertainment industry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:49
msgid ""
"Handling of freeform surfaces: Mesh-based systems are better equipped to "
"handle freeform surfaces, such as those found in organic shapes, as they do "
"not rely on mathematical representation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:52
msgid ""
"Handling of large datasets: Mesh-based systems are more suitable for "
"handling large datasets such as point clouds, as they can be easily "
"converted into a mesh representation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:57
msgid "Parameterized Models"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:59
msgid ""
"Parametrized CAD systems are more effective than non-parametric CAD systems "
"in several ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:62
msgid ""
"Reusability: Parametrized CAD models can be easily modified by changing a "
"set of parameters, such as the length or width of an object, rather than "
"having to manually edit the geometry. This makes it easy to create "
"variations of a design without having to start from scratch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:66
msgid ""
"Design exploration: Parametrized CAD systems allow for easy exploration of "
"different design options by changing the parameters and quickly visualizing "
"the results.  This can save a lot of time and effort during the design "
"process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:69
msgid ""
"Constraints and relationships: Parametrized CAD systems allow for the "
"definition of constraints and relationships between different parameters. "
"This ensures that the model remains valid and functional even when "
"parameters are changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:73
msgid ""
"Automation: Parametrized CAD systems can be automated to perform repetitive "
"tasks, such as generating detailed drawings or creating parts lists. This "
"can save a lot of time and effort and reduce the risk of errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:76
msgid ""
"Collaboration: Parametrized CAD systems allow different team members to work"
" on different aspects of a design simultaneously and ensure that the model "
"remains consistent across different stages of the development process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:79
msgid ""
"Document management: Parametrized CAD systems can generate engineering "
"drawings, BOMs, and other documents automatically, which makes it easier to "
"manage and track the design history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/introduction.rst:83
msgid ""
"In summary, parametrized CAD systems are more effective than non-parametric "
"CAD systems because they provide a more efficient and flexible way to create"
" and modify designs, and can be easily integrated into the design, "
"manufacturing, and documentation process."
msgstr ""

